data.content:
noun
plural ~ spots
[count] an area around a car, truck, etc., that the driver cannot see
When driving on the highway, you need to make sure no one is in your blind spot before changing lanes.
a tendency to ignore something especially because it is difficult or unpleasant
She has a blind spot concerning her son's behavior.
a small area at the back of the eye that is not sensitive to light

vùng nhìn hạn chế
I didn't see the car that was overtaking me, it was my blind spot
tôi đã không thấy chiếc xe đang vượt qua, nó nằm đúng vào vùng nhìn hạn chế của tôi
điểm yếu
history is one of his blind spots
môn lịch sự là một trong những điểm yếu của hắn
(giải phẫu)
điểm mù
